[SN]TITLE[SN]
Leon Barnett: Bury sign former Wigan Athletic defender

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Bury have signed defender Leon Barnett on a two-year deal after his release by Wigan Athletic.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 30-year-old joined the Latics from Norwich City in 2013 and helped them win the League One title last season.
Barnett started his career with Luton Town before moving to West Bromwich Albion in 2007, where he won promotion to the Premier League in 2008.
He also won promotion to the top flight with Norwich in 2011 and with Cardiff during a loan spell in 2013.
